</ol>
<h2>14 local marketing trends and tactics for 2024</h2>
<p>‚ÄúLocal marketing in 2024 no longer means placing an ad in a local paper‚Äîalthough that can have its place,‚Äù said Magee Clegg, CEO of <a href="https://cleartailmarketing.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cleartail Marketing</a>.</p>
<p>‚ÄúIt&#8217;s more about focusing on strategies that emphasize long-term customer relationships, utilizing professional platforms and proactively managing your online reputation.‚Äù</p>
<p>Here are some <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/advertising-techniques">tactics</a>, trends, and ideas to help you build the most successful local marketing strategy for 2024.</p>
<div id="local-seo-optimization"></div>
<h3>1. Optimize your online presence for local SEO</h3>
<p>This isn‚Äôt necessarily a trend as Google Business Profiles have been around for 10 years (this year!), but it‚Äôs extremely important for any <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/15/local-marketing-ideas">local marketing</a> strategy. You still need to master the basics. This means <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/03/google-my-business-optimization">optimizing your Google Business Profile</a>, Apple Maps, and other local directories for local‚Äîand hyper-local‚ÄîSEO.</p>
<p>‚ÄúEnsuring your business appears in local search results, particularly your Google Business listing, can significantly increase visibility,‚Äù said Deepak Shukla, founder of SEO agency <a href="https://pearllemon.com/us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pearl Lemon</a>. ‚ÄúIn the post-pandemic era, where <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/online-presence/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">online presence</a> has become even more critical, this strategy is essential for attracting local customers.‚Äù</p>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/local-search-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Optimization tactics for local search include</a> the addition of hours, offerings, and reviews, which help <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/11/increase-conversion-rates">convert searchers</a> into customers, said Dan Dillon CEO of <a href="https://www.cleanitsupply.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CleanItSupply.com</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/google-business-profile-example-dentist-boston.jpg" alt="example of an optimized google business profile from a dentist in boston" width="920" height="492" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-71139" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/google-business-profile-example-dentist-boston.jpg 920w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/google-business-profile-example-dentist-boston-480x257.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 920px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This also helps businesses establish themselves as authoritative and build local trust, added Dmytro Sokhach, founder of digital marketing agency <a href="https://admixglobal.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Admix Global</a>.</p>
<p>As ‚Äúnear me‚Äù searches remain popular‚Äîmore than 60% of mobile searches have local intent, by some estimates‚ÄîKen Fortney, CEO of SEO firm <a href="https://www.thatlocalpack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">That Local Pack</a>, pointed to one New York restaurant, which saw a 270% increase in revenue in a single year by adopting an enhanced <a href="https://localiq.com/local-marketing-lab/seo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local SEO</a> strategy that included Google Business optimization, as well as customer reviews (more on that later) and location-specific menus.</p>
<p>‚ÄúConsumers are increasingly turning to local search to fulfill their immediate needs, and local SEO is key in attracting these ready-to-convert customers,‚Äù Fortney said.</p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4cd.png" alt="üìç" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Are your listings optimized for local search? </strong>Find out with our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/free-business-listings-grader?cid=Web_WS_InContentTextLink_Freemium_Listings&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent"><strong>Free Business Listings Grader</strong></a><strong>!</strong></p>
<div id="voice-search-optimization"></div>
<h3>2. Don‚Äôt forget voice search optimization</h3>
<p>In addition to local SEO basics, businesses should also integrate natural language processing to capitalize on voice queries.</p>
<p>‚ÄúThis involves utilizing conversational, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/long-tail-keywords">long-tail keywords</a> in content optimization, leading to a broader range of search visibility and potential customer attraction,‚Äù Fortney said.</p>
<p>For example, instead of targeting &#8220;Italian restaurants,&#8221; businesses could use &#8220;family-friendly Italian restaurant in Boston.&#8221;</p>
<p>‚ÄúThis hyper-personalization targets the <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/niche-markets/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">niche audience</a> directly and increases conversion probability,‚Äù added Gianluca Ferruggia, general manager of B2B marketplace <a href="https://www.designrush.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DesignRush</a>.</p>
<p>And don‚Äôt forget <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/09/15/what-is-schema-markup">Schema markup</a>.</p>
<p>‚ÄúOptimizing for local pack rankings with precise location-based keywords and building <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/localize-google-ads">localized</a> links from directory listings and community websites is key,‚Äù said Lyn Collanto, marketing specialist at SEO agency <a href="https://kbaweb.com.au/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">KBA Web</a>. ‚ÄúAs mobile and voice search continue to rise, enhancing on-site elements like click-to-call and direction links will also be impactful.‚Äù</p>
<div id="local-influencers"></div>
<h3>3. Tap into local influencers</h3>
<p>While the benefits of using influencers to connect with consumers is widely documented, collaborating with local influencers, which may have smaller audiences, can be a big boon to local marketing.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/content-creators-influencer.png" alt="content creator - screenshot of an influencer's post" width="640" height="429" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75863" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/content-creators-influencer.png 640w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/content-creators-influencer-480x322.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 640px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>‚ÄúIncluding local micro-influencers in marketing campaigns can yield positive results,‚Äù Ferruggia said. ‚ÄúTheir niche, dedicated following helps generate trustworthy <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/06/26/word-of-mouth-marketing">word-of-mouth</a> in the respective community.‚Äù</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f440.png" alt="üëÄ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Looking for more ways to drive people to your site? Free guide &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite25WaysIncreaseTraffic.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_25WaysIncreaseTraffic_Download">25 Ways to Increase Traffic to Your Website</a></p>
<div id="local-events"></div>
<h3>4. Host, sponsor, or attend local events</h3>
<p>In addition to local influencers, local events are a good strategy to think about.</p>
<p>Examples include hosting workshops or classes, such as a cake decorating tutorial at a bakery.</p>
<p>‚ÄúThese events attract potential customers and create a memorable experience associated with your brand,‚Äù said Randy VanderVaate, CEO of <a href="http://www.funeralfunds.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Funeral Funds of America</a>.</p>
<p>‚ÄúBy partnering with local influencers and businesses and hosting or sponsoring local events, a company can effectively tap into the local audience,‚Äù Shukla said. ‚ÄúThese strategies not only enhance community engagement but also foster a sense of solidarity and support, which is particularly valuable in the current times where there&#8217;s a strong desire for community connection.‚Äù</p>
<p>In fact, Dillon believes community partnerships will grow in importance as these events help foster trust and authenticity.</p>
<p>Geoff Cudd, founder of review site <a href="https://ddiy.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Don&#8217;t Do It Yourself</a>, agreed businesses that engage in local events, sponsor local teams or partner with other local businesses can see a boost in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/02/06/online-reputation-management">reputation</a> and loyalty.</p>
<p>‚ÄúThis approach not only increases brand visibility but also builds a strong local network,‚Äù he added.</p>
<p>That could even include a cross-promotional offer with another local business.</p>
<p>‚ÄúBrands that engage in local community initiatives or partner with other local businesses to create combined offerings may witness higher customer loyalty and differentiate themselves in the bustling marketplace,‚Äù said Pavel Naydenov, head of marketing at software platform <a href="https://businessmap.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Businessmap</a>.</p>
<p>Per his figures, Oleg Segal, CEO of discount site <a href="https://deala.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DealA</a>, said he has seen a 45% increase in these local partnerships in recent months.</p>
<div id="reviews-and-online-reputation"></div>
<h3>5. Prioritize reviews</h3>
<p>Along the way, encourage customers to leave <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/16/how-to-ask-for-reviews">online reviews</a> on platforms like Google and Yelp. A solid presence here can contribute to a successful local <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-strategy-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing strategy</a>.</p>
<p>That‚Äôs in part because local sentiment and word-of-mouth lives online now. And so it‚Äôs important to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-respond-to-google-reviews-with-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">address both positive and negative reviews</a> instead of trying to bury the latter.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-review-response-example.webp" alt="example of negative google review response" width="936" height="450" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-81267" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-review-response-example.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-review-response-example-480x231.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>‚ÄúActively listening, engaging positively, and addressing negative reviews is critical to maintaining community trust and loyalty,‚Äù said Iurii Nemtcev, CEO of <a href="https://biglab.ae/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Big Lab Digital Agency</a>.</p>
<div id="social-media-communities"></div>
<h3>6. Engage with social media communities</h3>
<p>In addition to advertising on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/social-media-strategy">social media</a>, local businesses can use these platforms to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/19/brand-community">drive community engagement</a>.</p>
<p>‚ÄúSocial media platforms are increasingly becoming local hubs,‚Äù Shukla said. ‚ÄúEngaging with the community by promoting local events, participating in local discussions, and showcasing community involvement can build a loyal local following.‚Äù</p>
<div id="linkedin"></div>
<h3>7. Don‚Äôt underestimate the power of LinkedIn</h3>
<p>While <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/11/most-popular-social-media-platforms">social platforms</a> like Facebook and Instagram remain popular among local marketers‚Äî<a href="https://localiq.com/blog/facebook-ads-for-small-business/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">and for good reasons</a>‚ÄîClegg called LinkedIn ‚Äúa potent platform for local businesses looking to expand their reach.‚Äù</p>
<p>That‚Äôs in part because <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/01/25/optimize-linkedin-ads">LinkedIn</a> outreach can deliver enhanced results when combined with emails. For one client, Clegg added 400 emails per month and scheduled 40 qualified sales calls per month as a result of implementing this tactic.</p>
<div id="hyper-local-advertising"></div>
<h3>8. Run hyper-local advertising</h3>
<p>Beyond engaging communities on social media, tap into the power of these platforms to target your ads to local consumers.</p>
<p>‚ÄúPlatforms like Facebook and Instagram offer <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/09/13/facebook-ad-targeting-privacy-first-world">advanced targeting options</a> that allow businesses to reach potential customers in specific geographic areas,‚Äù Cudd said. ‚ÄúBy creating localized content and ads, businesses can effectively engage with a community-focused audience.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/google-ads-for-real-estate-ab-test-example.webp" alt="google ads for real estate ab test example" width="936" height="567" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76253" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/google-ads-for-real-estate-ab-test-example.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/google-ads-for-real-estate-ab-test-example-480x291.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>An example of a localized ad vs. a generic ad for the same business.</em></p>
<p>The result is the personalized content consumers crave‚Äîand can reach potential customers with a high potential for engagement.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want to learn about local ads on Google? Get the free guide &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLPPC101.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_PPC101_Download">PPC 101: Complete Guide to Google Ads</a></p>
<div id="data-driven-hyper-local-targeting"></div>
<h3>9. Use data and analytics to create more powerful hyper-local targeting</h3>
<p>Hyper-local targeting will get a boost in 2024 thanks to more advanced data analytics.</p>
<p>‚ÄúIn 2024, the key is hyper-local targeting, using advanced data analytics to understand and engage with specific demographics within a community,‚Äù said Leena Sowambur, founder of Marcomms by Leena.</p>
<p>What‚Äôs more, the ability to combine <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/04/customer-segmentation-models">consumer data points</a>‚Äîsuch as shopping habits, online behavior and even political leanings‚Äîwill fuel more personalized messaging.</p>
<p>‚ÄúWe&#8217;re seeing an unprecedented emphasis on cross-sectional marketing,‚Äù she added. ‚ÄúThis strategy allows for nuanced messaging that resonates deeply with diverse groups within a community.‚Äù</p>
<div id="video"></div>
<h3>10. Invest in video</h3>
<p>Local businesses that want to take their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/content-marketing-trends-2024">content marketing</a> efforts up a notch should consider video, which remains the format of choice across social media.</p>
<p>‚ÄúThis trend offers businesses new opportunities to creatively engage with their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">target audiences</a>, revolutionizing how they connect with viewers,‚Äù said Zain Bin Zameer, senior link-building expert at Technology Ally. ‚ÄúWhether through product demos, brand stories or educational tutorials, the impact of video content is set to reshape the marketing landscape for years to come.‚Äù</p>
<p>In addition, Dillon suggested small businesses experiment with formats like short-form or live videos to capitalize on platforms like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/14/tiktok-trend-discovery">TikTok</a> and Reels.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tiktok-trend-discovery-married-in-italy-trend.jpg" alt="tiktok trend discovery - example of business using tiktok trend" width="281" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78535" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tiktok-trend-discovery-married-in-italy-trend.jpg 281w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/tiktok-trend-discovery-married-in-italy-trend-141x300.jpg 141w" sizes="(max-width: 281px) 100vw, 281px" /></p>
<p>‚ÄúThese strategies will harness not only <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/digital-marketing-trends-2024/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">digital trends</a> but also market shifts in consumer behavior and technological advancements,‚Äù he added.</p>
<div id="local-marketing-ai-tools"></div>
<h3>11. Use AI tools</h3>
<p>While the benefits of video content are well-documented, high-quality video isn‚Äôt always affordable.</p>
<p>However, thanks to the advent of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-tools-for-marketing-agency">AI tools</a>, we‚Äôre going to see further democratization of high-quality video content in 2024.</p>
<p>That‚Äôs according to Lucas Ochoa, CEO of <a href="https://www.runautomat.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Automat</a>, who said, ‚ÄúWhat used to be an expensive and exclusive process is becoming more accessible and affordable. This shift won&#8217;t just level the playing field for local businesses but will also usher in a fresh wave of creativity and personalization in marketing communications.‚Äù</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f916.png" alt="ü§ñ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want to use AI the right way? <strong>Free download &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteAIinMarketingGuide.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_AIMarketing_Download">Emergency Guide to AI in Marketing</a></p>
<div id="diversified-local-content"></div>
<h3>12. Create diversified local content</h3>
<p>But geo-targeted content like emails and texts can also be powerful tools.</p>
<p>‚ÄúMost importantly, producing consistent, high-quality local content tailored to the area and offering real value to nearby searchers is what can propel SEO success for local businesses in the ever-evolving local search landscape,‚Äù Collanto said. ‚ÄúFocusing initiatives around these types of local marketing strategies and trends will yield the best results.‚Äù</p>
<div id="learn-from-b2b-tactics"></div>
<h3>13. Learn from B2B tactics</h3>
<p>Even B2C brands will want to pay attention to this one.</p>
<p>As consumer behavior continues to go digital and data-driven marketing tactics proliferate, local advertisers have an opportunity to embrace <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/b2b-marketing-trends-2024">B2B marketing strategies</a> to expand their reach.</p>
<p>‚ÄúThe concept takes a bit of a pivot from traditional B2C strategies‚Äîit views every local customer as a potential business partner,‚Äù Clegg said. ‚ÄúIn practice, we helped our clients build stronger relationships with local customers and offered them value beyond a single transaction, converting them into long-term advocates for the business.‚Äù</p>
<div id="personalize-content-and-promotions"></div>
<h3>14. Personalize and segment content and promotions</h3>
<p>Finally, brands that sell products online have an opportunity in what Sunny Zheng, senior manager at cosmetic brand <a href="https://www.tyoemcosmetic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tengyu</a>, called ‚Äúpersonalized local ecommerce.‚Äù</p>
<p>By creating web pages with content and deals specifically for target regions via its Regional Specials project, Tengyu netted 2000 additional online sales in three months.</p>
<p>‚ÄúIt shows how much people appreciate content that feels personally relevant to them,‚Äù Zheng said.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2024-digital-marketing-trends-glocal-approach-canes-example.webp" alt="glocal marketing example raising cane's" width="936" height="481" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79430" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2024-digital-marketing-trends-glocal-approach-canes-example.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2024-digital-marketing-trends-glocal-approach-canes-example-480x247.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>Build the best local marketing strategy for 2024</h2>
<p>Using these expert-approved local marketing trends and tips, you can build a strategy that gets you seen by the right local audience.</p>
<p>Here are the best local marketing trends, tips, and strategies for 2024:</p>
<ol>
<li>Optimize your online presence for local SEO</li>
<li>Don‚Äôt forget voice search optimization</li>
<li>Tap into local influencers</li>
<li>Host, sponsor, or attend local events</li>
<li>Prioritize reviews</li>
<li>Engage with social media communities</li>
<li>Don‚Äôt underestimate the power of LinkedIn</li>
<li>Run hyper-local advertising</li>
<li>Use data and analytics to create more powerful hyper-local targeting</li>
<li>Invest in video</li>
<li>Use AI tools</li>
<li>Create diversified local content</li>
<li>Learn from B2B tactics</li>
<li>Personalize and segment content and promotions</li>
</ol>
