		<item>
		<title>Google Ads Rolling Out Enhancements to Location Assets: Here&#8217;s How to Use It</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/07/google-ads-location-assets-enhancements</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 13:30:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Google Ads]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Local Marketing]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=75832</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Google Ads new enhancement to location assets pulls an image from a business's Google Business Profile into its ad. Find out how to use this enhancement (or how to opt out).</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/07/google-ads-location-assets-enhancements">Google Ads Rolling Out Enhancements to Location Assets: Here&#8217;s How to Use It</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Location Assets (formerly known as <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2011/09/19/adwords-location-extensions-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Location Extensions</a>) have been a staple of any good local business‚Äôs Google Ads account for over a decade. Although their name has changed a few times since their introduction, they‚Äôve always functioned the same and served the same value‚Äìsimply link your Google Business Profile to Google Ads and your ads will begin to show your location to searchers nearby.</p>
<p>After decades of this simple but effective design, Google recently began automatically enhancing its location assets to <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/2404182?utm_source=awfe&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=20249167#merchant_photos&amp;zippy=%2Copt-out-of-using-merchant-photos-in-local-ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">include an image of their local business</a> alongside their address and hours. This new feature is designed to help your ads stand out on the busy SERP, improve ad performance, and reinforce trust in your local business.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example.jpg" alt="google ads location assets enhancements - example via google search" width="936" height="330" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75836" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-480x169.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://twitter.com/darcyburk/status/1674408251935318017/photo/2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll walk through:</p>
<ul>
<li>How to feature your business&#8217;s images in your Google Ads location assets</li>
<li>Best practices for your business&#8217;s images in location assets</li>
<li>How to opt out of showing your images in location assets</li>
</ul>
<p>Let&#8217;s get started.</p>
<h2>How to feature your business&#8217;s images in your Google Ads location assets</h2>
<p>To take advantage of this new feature, all advertisers need to do is maintain their Google Business Profile, have it linked to Google Ads, and have their location extensions active in their campaigns. Google will automatically highlight any of your Google Business Profile‚Äôs merchant photos.</p>
<p>Your Google Ads location <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-assets">assets</a> will only include images that you‚Äôve uploaded directly to your GBP‚Äôs Merchant Photos‚Äìit will not pull any photos submitted to your GBP from past visitors or from reviews, so you‚Äôll always set the right impression with your ads‚Äô images.</p>
<h3>1. Create and manage your Google Business Profile‚Äôs merchant photos</h3>
<p>For your Google Ads‚Äô location assets to feature your business‚Äôs images, you‚Äôll first need to upload at least one merchant photo to your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/08/what-is-google-my-business" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Business Profile</a>. To upload merchant photos, first sign into your Google Business Profile and select ‚ÄúAdd Photo.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-merchant-photo.jpg" alt="location assets google ads - where to manage images for merchant center" width="936" height="411" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75837" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-merchant-photo.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-merchant-photo-480x211.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>2. Upload your images</h3>
<p>You‚Äôll then have three options for the type of photo to upload.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Logo: </strong>Your logo photo will help you keep your brand consistent and identifiable across Google. Your logo icon will appear alongside any posts from your profile or anytime you respond to a question or review.</li>
<li><strong>Cover photo: </strong>Your cover photo is the money shot ‚Äì this photo is most likely to show up first in your Google Business Profile listing and will be used the most in your Google location assets images.</li>
<li><strong>Photo: </strong>These are supplementary photos that will show in your Google Business Profile listing. They‚Äôre often visible alongside your Cover photo, so it‚Äôs worth including at least several different and dynamic images of your business.</li>
</ul>
<h3>3. Remove outdated photos</h3>
<p>If your business photos are outdated or poor quality, you can also remove any old photos from your Google Business Profile. Just log into your Google Business Profile and select anywhere in the photos section. Navigate to the ‚ÄúBy owner‚Äù section and select the photo you wish to remove. In the top right corner, you should be able to select a trash can ‚Äúdelete‚Äù icon to remove it from your profile.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-remove-google-business-image.jpg" alt="location assets enhancement - remove google business image from profile" width="936" height="572" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75844" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-remove-google-business-image.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-remove-google-business-image-480x293.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Are your Google Ads missing the mark? Find out with a free, instant audit from our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Grader</a>!</div></div>
<h2>Best practices for Google Business Profile photos and Google Ads location assets</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/03/google-my-business-optimization">Optimizing your Google Business Profile</a> isn‚Äôt just important for your Google Ads location assets. Your Google Business Profile is likely the first thing searchers will see when they find you online, and it‚Äôs a huge part of Google‚Äôs own <a href="https://localiq.com/local-marketing-lab/seo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local SEO</a> ranking algorithm.</p>
<p>Spend the time to completely fill out your Google Business Profile and regularly update it to highlight to both Google and searchers alike that you‚Äôre an active, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-respond-to-google-reviews-with-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">responsive</a>, and trustworthy business.</p>
<h3>1. Prioritize a high-quality cover photo</h3>
<p>Your cover photo will usually be shown first and most prominently on the SERP, alongside your GBP, and now alongside your Google Ads. Ensure that your cover photo best represents the image of your brand and is accurate to your business. Use proper lighting, focus, and minimal alterations. Google recommends your cover photo to be at least 720 x 720 in size.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-plumbing.jpg" alt="location assets enhancements - example of ad with image as part of location asset" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75848" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-plumbing.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-plumbing-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>2. Include a variety of different photos</h3>
<p>Your cover photo may get the most attention, but it won‚Äôt always show alone. A prospective visitor is likely to browse several images online before visiting in person. Consider including:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Several exterior images: </strong>To help customers recognize your business as they approach. Include different images to highlight how your storefront looks from different directions, parking and transit options, as well as how your business looks at night.</li>
<li><strong>Interior images: </strong>To highlight the atmosphere that customers should expect in your store. Highlight color product displays, seasonal areas, waiting rooms, common areas, and amenities that customers may want to see.</li>
<li><strong>Staff photos: </strong>To highlight your great team and present a more personal side of your business. Authentic photos that show your team working together earns trust in your business. Avoid including formal headshots.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-best-practices-images.jpg" alt="example of google business images for boston real estate agent" width="533" height="598" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75846" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-best-practices-images.jpg 533w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-best-practices-images-480x539.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 533px, 100vw" /></p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'>Make sure your listings are up to par with LocaliQ&#8217;s <a href="https://localiq.com/free-business-listings-grader/?cid=Web_WS_InContentTextLink_Freemium_Listings&amp;utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=freemium" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Business Listings Grader</a> <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2705.png" alt="‚úÖ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></div></div>
<h3>3. Create a Google Ads Logo asset</h3>
<p>Your Google Business Profile will highlight your logo alongside your posts and responses automatically. You also highlight that same logo alongside all your Google ads to reinforce your brand consistently on the SERP. Creating a logo asset is a simple and effective way to improve your ads performance, but you‚Äôll need to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/13/google-advertiser-verification">verify your Google Ads account</a> before you can implement it.<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-logo-asset.jpg" alt="location assets - google logo asset" width="701" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75838" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-logo-asset.jpg 701w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-logo-asset-480x411.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 701px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>4. Enhance your ads with image assets</h3>
<p>Your location assets and images from your Google Business Profile will automatically appear when a user is searching for you locally‚Äìbut searchers outside of your area may not always see these assets.</p>
<p>Include <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/21/google-ads-image-extensions">image assets</a> in your Google Ads campaigns to provide more visual aspects to your search ads, whether or not a user is searching locally or not. Image assets are also more flexible and don‚Äôt need to be directly related to your physical location.</p>
<p>Use them to highlight images of more seasonal events, sales, products, and services that wouldn‚Äôt always be appropriate to be prominently displayed on your Google Business Profile.</p>
<h2>How to opt out of automatically including photos in your local Google Ads</h2>
<p>Some businesses won‚Äôt always have the most aesthetic Google Business Profile photos and may want to opt out of including photos of their location within Google Ads. Luckily for them, these new features for location assets can be turned off and allow advertisers to just show their location alongside their ad without any photos.</p>
<p>To opt out of automatically including photos in your local Google Ads, follow these steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Within Google Ads, select ‚ÄúAds and Assets‚Äù from the left-hand bar, then select ‚ÄúAssets.‚Äù</li>
<li>Under the ‚ÄúAssociations view,‚Äù select the 3-dot ‚ÄúMore‚Äù icon. Then select ‚ÄúAccount-level automated assets.‚Äù</li>
<li>From this view, select the three-dot ‚ÄúMore‚Äù icon again. Now select the option ‚ÄúAdvanced settings‚Äù</li>
<li>Under ‚ÄúAutomatic locations,‚Äù there is a check box to ‚ÄúGrant Google Ads license to use merchant photos and other rich media from the linked Google Business Profiles in the advertising campaigns from this account.‚Äù Unselect this option and hit save. This will prevent Google from pulling any photos from your Google Business Profile to serve alongside your ads.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Show off your business images in location assets</h2>
<p>These new enhancements to location assets should be valuable for local advertisers and help their ads stick out from their competition on the SERP. As these features continue to roll out to more advertisers, now is a perfect time to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/optimize-google-my-business-listing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">review your Google Business Profile</a> and ensure your business is prominently displayed in local searches.</p>
