										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Back in the olden days, you‚Äôd leaf through a huge phone book to find a pet groomer, dentist, or roofer.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-meme-phonebooks-1.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - Meme about getting a number from a phonebook" width="795" height="599" class="aligncenter wp-image-73408 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-meme-phonebooks-1.jpg 795w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-meme-phonebooks-1-480x362.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 795px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The internet lifted business listings off of the Yellow Pages, made them digital, and put them on hyper mode. Now you might find the same roofer listed on dozens of directories, search engine results, and map app screens.</p>
<p>These listings are a boon to local businesses, delivering ready-to-buy customers right to your front door.</p>
<p>But what happens if the information on a directory or map search is wrong? Or if it‚Äôs missing altogether? Those people searching will head right to your competitor&#8217;s listing.</p>
<p>That‚Äôs where local listings management tools come in. Built with a variety of features, listings management tools help you monitor and update your company&#8217;s details on the places people search. They give you data about how people find and interact with your listings. And some even let you track and respond to reviews so your ratings go, well, through the roof.</p>
<h2>7 listings management tools to try</h2>
<p>Not all listing management tools are the same. Some are a feature of the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/03/01/business-directory-listings">business listings site</a> itself, like Google‚Äôs tools for managing the way people find your business on the search engine. Others give you the power to see and control dozens of listings in many locations all at once.</p>
<h3>1. Google Business Profile</h3>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-business-profile-updates-for-2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Business Profile</a> (GBP) is Google‚Äôs native tool for managing your listings on both Google Search and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-maps-mobile">Google Maps</a>. GBP‚Äôs features let you improve your search results and communicate with people interested in your business.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-GBP-intro.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - screenshot of Google Business Profile landing page" width="936" height="477" class="aligncenter wp-image-73409 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-GBP-intro.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-GBP-intro-480x245.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h4>Google listing optimization</h4>
<p>The more information you have in your Google Business Profile, the better the chance you have of nabbing some traffic-generating real estate on search and maps results pages. GBP helps you <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/03/google-my-business-optimization">optimize your profile</a> to make it more search engine-friendly.</p>
<p>For example, you can add a <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-write-a-business-description/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">business description</a> and category that gives customers and search engines more context about your company. GBP also lets you add photos to spice up text-only profiles.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-example-optimized-GBP.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - example of a profile before and after optimization" width="865" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73410 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-example-optimized-GBP.jpg 865w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-example-optimized-GBP-480x333.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 865px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The great thing about GBP is that you only need to update your profile once. It‚Äôll show those changes on Google Maps, search results, and in the coveted <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/get-your-business-on-google-3-pack/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local 3-pack</a>.</p>
<h4>Message management</h4>
<p>Your Google Business Profile offers a couple of ways to engage with your customers on a one-to-one level.</p>
<p>First off, you can read and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-respond-to-google-reviews-with-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">respond to reviews</a> using GBP. Since reviews and ratings are prominently presented in results, you‚Äôll want to make sure and keep up with them.</p>
<p>There is also the option to add direct messaging to your GBP profile. That gives you a way to answer more detailed follow-up questions (and hopefully gain more customers!).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-GBP-reviews.jpg" alt="Listings management tools" width="400" height="597" class="aligncenter wp-image-73411 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-GBP-reviews.jpg 400w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-GBP-reviews-201x300.jpg 201w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.google.com/business/?ppsrc=GPDA2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>And finally, you can add an FAQ section to your profile.</p>
<p>Answering frequently asked questions not only helps the person asking, but it also gives helpful information to anyone reading through your profile.</p>
<h3>2. LocaliQ Listings</h3>
<p>LocaliQ offers business listing management that puts you in control of how your business is seen on more than 50 different directories and websites.</p>
<p>The platform offers three ways to generate more sales from local business listing directories.</p>
<h4>Local listings management</h4>
<p>One of the most helpful features of LocaliQ&#8217;s listings management solution is its <a href="https://localiq.com/products/listings/?itm_source=localiq&amp;itm_medium=mega_menu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">listings management tool</a>. With a single click, you can update your business details to dozens of directories.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs how it works. Let&#8217;s say you decide to add a new service and extend your operating hours on Saturdays. Normally, you‚Äôd have to go into Google, Yelp, Bing, and all the other directories to manually edit your citation.</p>
<p>With LocaliQ‚Äôs listings management tool, you type those changes in your dashboard, then syndicate them to each of those websites automatically.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-profile.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - screenshot of LocaliQs profile checker" width="654" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73414 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-profile.jpg 654w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-profile-480x440.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 654px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You can also use LocaliQ to look for and remove SEO-killing duplicate listings and manage <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/multi-location-seo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">multiple location listings</a> from the same dashboard.</p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><p>Not sure if your listings are up to par? Use LocaliQ&#8217;s <a href="https://localiq.com/free-business-listings-grader/?utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=freemium">Free Business Listings Grader</a> to find out.</p></div></div>
<h4>Review management</h4>
<p>Many directories like Google and Yelp give users the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/16/how-to-ask-for-reviews">ability to review your business</a>. It‚Äôs critical to read and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-deal-with-bad-reviews/#:~:text=Follow%20our%20steps%20for%20responding%20to%20negative%20reviews%2C,Offer%20a%20resolution.%20...%205%20Follow%20up.%20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">respond to those reviews</a>. But let‚Äôs face it, you‚Äôll spend all day trying to chase them down in each directory.</p>
<p>LocaliQ lets you read and respond to recent reviews from several directories, right in your dashboard.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-reviews.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - LocaliQ's review management dashboard" width="582" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73415 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-reviews.jpg 582w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-reviews-480x495.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 582px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You‚Äôll also see important aggregated customer feedback data, like your average review rating. If there‚Äôs a big change in that info, you can figure out what happened and react.</p>
<h4>Business listings analytics</h4>
<p>How do customers find you? LocaliQ‚Äôs reports show you if it was search engines, maps, or other sources that led them to your listing.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-analytics.jpg" alt="Listing management tools - LocalQ's analytics dashboard" width="445" height="439" class="aligncenter wp-image-73416 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-analytics.jpg 445w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-localiq-analytics-300x296.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 445px) 100vw, 445px" /></p>
<p>The easy-to-read reports include data on what actions people take after seeing your listings. Do they call? Or are they more inclined to click on your website?</p>
<h3>3. Yelp</h3>
<p>According to Yelp, <a href="https://business.yelp.com/resources/study-shows-high-intent-consumers-are-contacting-businesses-quickly-on-yelp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">80 million</a> people pop into its directory to find a business every month. And four out of five Yelp customers make a purchase within minutes of viewing a business‚Äôs profile. Yelp&#8217;s listing tools offer some unique ways to get more of those people to your door.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Yelp-intro.jpg" alt="Local listings management - Yelp for Business landing page" width="929" height="498" class="aligncenter wp-image-73417 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Yelp-intro.jpg 929w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Yelp-intro-480x257.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 929px, 100vw" /></p>
<h4>Review management</h4>
<p>Sure, Yelp is a directory. But it‚Äôs first and foremost a review website. Users can leave reviews, <a href="https://blog.yelp.com/community/welcome-to-the-elite-squad-faqs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">become elite reviewers</a>, and even review the reviews. So it‚Äôs no surprise that Yelp provides review management tools.</p>
<p>Once you <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-claim-a-business-on-yelp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">claim your Yelp listing</a>, you can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2013/07/22/yelp-reviews" target="_blank" rel="noopener">respond directly to any review</a> your business receives through the Yelp dashboard.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-review-1.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - Yelp review example" width="930" height="453" class="aligncenter wp-image-73419 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-review-1.jpg 930w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-review-1-480x234.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 930px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.yelp.com/biz/california-pizza-kitchen-at-prudential-boston-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>If you want to take the conversation out of public view, Yelp lets you get direct messages‚Äîincluding requests for quotes, phone calls, or consultations‚Äîfrom customers.</p>
<h4>Business updates</h4>
<p>Listings can get stale over time. Yelp‚Äôs listing management tool lets you add updates to your profile to get people excited about what you offer.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Yelp-connect.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - Yelp connect example" width="606" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73421 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Yelp-connect.jpg 606w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Yelp-connect-480x475.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 606px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Officially, the feature is called Yelp Connect. With it, you can add little image icons that look like <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/instagram-story-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram Story Highlights</a>. Users hover over them to read whatever delicious detail you‚Äôve shared.</p>
<h3>4. Bing Places</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.bingplaces.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bing Places</a> is Microsoft&#8217;s answer to the Google Business Profile. While Bing Places can‚Äôt boast the functionality of GBP, it does have a few listing management tools to help you get found by <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/11/19/who-uses-bing-anyway#_ga=2.121975054.401447745.1688386652-497116163.1684162194&amp;_gac=1.53142234.1686663326.CjwKCAjwp6CkBhB_EiwAlQVyxVvyIjqPK9-OmjpTaQmFh2CJ2UJHvPlYTFzYFKz4ld9cyYhUrvRnwhoC_d0QAvD_BwE">more people than you may suspect</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Bing-intro.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - Bing Places landing page" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73422 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Bing-intro.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Bing-intro-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h4>Listing information management</h4>
<p>If you‚Äôre not using a listings management tool like the one offered by LocaliQ, you‚Äôll need to hop into Bing every once in a while to make sure your information is correct.</p>
<p>Just like for Google, you need to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-claim-your-bing-business-listing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">claim your listing on Bing first</a>. But then Bing lets you fill in all the juicy details like hours of operation and so forth. The really cool bit is that you can just import all of that data right from your Google Business profile to save time.</p>
<p>Once you‚Äôre up and running, you‚Äôll be eligible for placement on Bing Search and Maps.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Bing-location-map-1.jpg" alt="listings management tools - Bing map" width="936" height="569" class="aligncenter wp-image-73424 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Bing-location-map-1.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Bing-location-map-1-480x292.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>And bonus: You may even land yourself as the result in upcoming voice searches since Bing powers both Microsoft‚Äôs Cortana and Amazon‚Äôs Alexa.</p>
<h3>5. Facebook Business Page</h3>
<p>The social media website functions like a local business directory because <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-promote-your-facebook-page-for-free/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook Business Pages</a> often wind up in search engine results. Luckily, Facebook offers some tools that‚Äôll help you manage your page as if it were a local listing.</p>
<h4>Location management</h4>
<p>It‚Äôs all about ‚Äúlocation, location, location‚Äù in local search results. So your Facebook page <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/add-location-to-facebook/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">needs to be linked to a geographic location</a> for it to show up in ‚Äú&#8230;near me‚Äù searches.</p>
<p>Facebook‚Äôs Business Page tools let you do that in a few ways. First and foremost, you can add your address to your Page.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Facebook-location-map.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - Facebook map" width="563" height="595" class="aligncenter wp-image-73425 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Facebook-location-map.jpg 563w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Facebook-location-map-480x507.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 563px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Facebook also lets you tag posts and images‚Äîon both desktop and mobile‚Äîwith a location. Then you can change the category of your business to one that works locally, like a plumber or hair stylist, so your business shows up when people filter for places, as opposed to people or posts.</p>
<h3>6. The Real Yellow Pages</h3>
<p>Yes, they‚Äôre still around. In fact, the <a href="https://www.yellowpages.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YP website</a> claims 4 billion searches for local businesses on its website and app each year. And there are some nice tools for businesses to manage their listings on the OG directory.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-intro.jpg" alt="Listings management page - YellowPages for business landing page" width="935" height="434" class="aligncenter wp-image-73426 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-intro.jpg 935w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-intro-480x223.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 935px, 100vw" /></p>
<h4>Multi-directory listing</h4>
<p>The YellowPages network actually includes three directories: The Real Yellow Pages, Superpages, and dexknows.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-network.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - graphic of yellowpages network" width="935" height="232" class="aligncenter wp-image-73427 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-network.jpg 935w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-network-480x119.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 935px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>That means any work you put into creating your business&#8217;s listing will automatically apply to all three locations for much more reach.</p>
<p>As for the listings themselves, YP gives you some options to customize <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/04/12/local-citations">citations</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-listing.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - yellowpages business citation" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73428 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-listing.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-YellowPages-listing-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You can add branding, images, action links, and special offers along with all the standard business info. There‚Äôs also plenty of space to write a full business description and include customer reviews.</p>
<h3>7. Foursquare</h3>
<p><a href="https://business.foursquare.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Foursquare</a> isn‚Äôt what you think it is anymore. What was once a social media app for telling your friends which boba tea joint to find you in has become the location data provider for some of the largest geographic-dependent apps in the world (think: Uber and Nextdoor). So when you claim your business listing on Foursquare, you‚Äôre giving your business more opportunities to show up in the apps that matter.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Foursquare-intro.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - Foursquare for business landing page" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73429 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Foursquare-intro.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Foursquare-intro-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h4>Socially networked listings</h4>
<p>Even though it doesn‚Äôt operate like a social media platform anymore, there‚Äôs still a network effect to the listings on Foursquare. In large part, that‚Äôs due to the ‚Äútips‚Äù feature of the app.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Foursquare-tips-2.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - Foursquare tip from user" width="658" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73430 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Foursquare-tips-2.jpg 658w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-Foursquare-tips-2-480x438.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 658px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The idea is that customers can offer those little insider suggestions that help new visitors get the most out of their trip.</p>
<p>The tips feature encourages people to add their favorite places to Foursquare, which means your local business may already have a citation there. You just need to <a href="https://foursquare.com/venue/claim" target="_blank" rel="noopener">claim it</a> and fill in the details‚Äîa task Foursquare makes easy with their listing management tool.</p>
<h4>Individualized analytics</h4>
<p>Like some of the other tools on this list, Foursquare also lets you track the analytics collected through each citation visit. But since people still check in to Foursquare leaving reviews and tips, the app has a lot of data about individual users. So you can not only tell how many people saw and clicked on your Foursquare listing, you can tell how often or how recently some of them walked through your door.</p>
<h2>Why local listings management tools are important</h2>
<p>Whether you‚Äôre using a tool like LocaliQ to manage many listings at once, or tackling each directory separately, listing management tools make it easy to view, manage, and track how you‚Äôre seen in directories. Here are some more reasons listings management tools are so important in finding <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/hot-leads-vs-cold-leads">hot leads</a>.</p>
<h3>Increase online presence</h3>
<p>Being present in online directories gets you access to more customers, can boost your SEO, and gives you more opportunities to collect reviews. That‚Äôs pretty important since <a href="https://www.invespcro.com/blog/the-importance-of-online-customer-reviews-infographic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">72%</a> of consumers say positive reviews make them trust a business more.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-stat-trust.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - graphic saying 72% of people say positive reviews make them trust businesses more" width="936" height="361" class="aligncenter wp-image-73432 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-stat-trust.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-stat-trust-480x185.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Millions of people use online directories to find local businesses. The more of those directories that include your business listing, the greater the chance you‚Äôll be found by new customers.</p>
<p>Search engines also reward businesses that have more, fully optimized citations and reviews on trusted directories.</p>
<p>Local listing management tools help you get cited on more directory websites and map apps.</p>
<h3>Maintain correct listing information</h3>
<p>Your business likely exists on many directories whether you put it there or not. That means the information displayed might be incorrect, out-of-date, and downright unflattering.</p>
<p>All that bad information will frustrate customers and signal search engines that your business isn‚Äôt trusted as your competitors (which we know isn‚Äôt true!). In fact, <a href="https://www.brightlocal.com/research/business-listings-trust-report/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">63%</a> of consumers say incorrect information would stop them from using that business.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-stat-incorrect.jpg" alt="Listings management tools - graphic saying 63% of people don't use businesses with incorrect listings" width="936" height="370" class="aligncenter wp-image-73433 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-stat-incorrect.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Listings-management-tools-stat-incorrect-480x190.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>When you use listing management tools, you can make sure your details are correct and even spice up your listings to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/17/halloween-greetings-sayingsundefined" target="_blank" rel="noopener">attract more customers</a>.</p>
<h3>Understand the trends</h3>
<p>Many of the listing tools we‚Äôve reviewed provide analytics. This peak behind the directory curtain clues you in on who‚Äôs visiting and where they‚Äôre coming from.</p>
<p>With these insights, you‚Äôll know which directories to focus on, which may need to be updated, and which delivers the <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-lower-cost-per-lead/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cheapest leads</a>. And if one directory seems to generate lots of reviews, it may lead you to spend on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/pay-per-click-advertising">paid ads</a> there.</p>
<h2>Get cited, found, and reviewed with listing management tools</h2>
<p>Online directories have helped millions of people <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-get-leads-for-any-business/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">connect with local businesses</a> like yours. The challenge for you is figuring out how to keep up with all of the places your business can be found (and all the <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/insurance-leads/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">leads</a> you&#8217;ll get).</p>
<p>To get started, consider using these local listings management tools:</p>
<ul>
<li>LocaliQ</li>
<li>Google Business Profile</li>
<li>Yelp</li>
<li>Bing Places</li>
<li>Facebook Business</li>
<li>The Real Yellow Pages</li>
<li>Foursquare</li>
</ul>
