<h3><strong>9. Facebook</strong></h3>
<p>Believe it or not, your most valuable doctor review site could be a social media platform like Facebook. While you may already be <a href="https://localiq.com/local-marketing-lab/facebook-ads/how-to-run-facebook-ads/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">running Facebook Ads</a> or posting organically on Facebook, you should also consider your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/10/16/facebook-business-page" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook business page</a> as a hub for users to find out more about your business and leave reviews.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/doctor-review-sites-facebook.jpg" alt="doctor review sites - facebook " width="900" height="462" class="aligncenter wp-image-72738 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/doctor-review-sites-facebook.jpg 900w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/doctor-review-sites-facebook-480x246.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw" /></p>
