					<description><![CDATA[<p>Show up for the right searches and be the business that gets chosen over competitors!</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/03/15/how-to-get-found-online-local-service-business">How to Get Found Online: Our Top 9 Tips for Local Service Businesses</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In today&#8217;s digital landscape, having a robust online presence is essential for businesses of all sizes, but especially those in the local service industry. With more people relying on search engines to find what they are looking for, businesses that are easily found online and have a solid online reputation will have a major advantage over their competitors.</p>
<p>So in this post, I‚Äôm going to show you how you can improve the local online presence of your service-based business using two fundamental marketing strategies: SEO and PPC</p>
<h2>The 9 best ways for local service businesses to get found online</h2>
<p>As a digital marketing instructor and consultatnt, I have had the privilege of not only teaching my students about the importance of combining search engine optimization (SEO) and pay-per-click (PPC) advertising for businesses, but also experiencing the positive impact of this combination firsthand. Here‚Äôs how to leverage these two strategies to drive traffic, generate leads, and maximize a limited budget.</p>
<h3>1. Pick the right company and domain name</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/23/how-to-come-up-with-a-business-name">Naming your business</a> should be a thoughtful process. You want something that reflects your brand personality and is not easily copyable.</p>
<p>As a local business, it can be extra helpful to pick something that aligns with your target audience‚Äôs search intent, but don‚Äôt force it. I once came across a dentist that named itself &#8220;Dentist Near Me&#8221; and secured the domain dentistnearme.com. Taking this approach to an extreme certainly has its SEO benefits but it may not always be the best idea as others may follow suit and adopt similar names, potentially rendering the strategy ineffective.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/dentist-near-me.jpeg" alt="dentist named &quot;dentist near me&quot;" width="720" height="513" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-70789" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/dentist-near-me.jpeg 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/dentist-near-me-480x342.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A6889968707662077952/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<p>A helpful tactic is to include your city, town, or service area name in your business name but it isn‚Äôt essential.</p>
<h3>2. Get your listings in order</h3>
<p>Having an up-to-date <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-business-profile-updates-for-2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Business Profile</a> is also a great way to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/17/increase-online-presence">improve your local business&#8217;s online presence</a>. Regularly update your business information, add photos, and create posts with deals and helpful articles to build trust and credibility with potential customers. You should follow suit for the rest of your online listings as well to increase your chances of <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-home-service-businesses-can-show-up-for-local-google-searches/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ranking in local searches</a>. You can use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/06/listings-management-tools">listings management tools</a> to simplify this.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/directory-listings-logos.png" alt="directory listing logos" width="720" height="245" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-70649" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/directory-listings-logos.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/directory-listings-logos-480x163.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This will make it easy for them to find and connect with you.</p>
<p><span><div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4cd.png" alt="üìç" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Are your listings optimized for local search? </span></p>
<p><span>Find out with our </span><strong><a href="https://localiq.com/free-business-listings-grader/?cid=Web_WS_InContentTextLink_Freemium_Listings&amp;utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=freemium" class="waffle-rich-text-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Business Listings Grader!</a></strong><span> </span></p>
<p><span></div></div></span></p>
<h3>3. Target keywords with blog posts</h3>
<p>Publish keyword-rich blog posts that answer common questions from potential customers‚Äînot just about your business specifically but about things related to the products and services you provide.</p>
<p>This will not only improve your website&#8217;s search engine ranking, but it will also build trust and credibility with potential customers.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/seo-trends-2023-on-page-seo.png" alt="seo trends 2023 - on page seo checklist" width="720" height="472" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-69436" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/seo-trends-2023-on-page-seo.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/seo-trends-2023-on-page-seo-480x315.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You can use our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/05/blog-post-templates">SEO-optimized blog post templates</a> to get started!</p>
<h3>4. Put your highest value CTA at the top right of your homepage</h3>
<p>Make sure your website is user-friendly and provides a great user experience. We have plenty of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/14/website-examples">website examples you can browse through here</a>. Implement prominent call-to-action buttons, such as a clickable a phone number in the top right-hand corner and footer, and a large contact form in the footer. These buttons are easily accessible, intuitive, and make it simple for customers to get in touch with you, book a lesson, start a free trial, etc.</p>
<p>Your highest value CTA should go in that right-hand section.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/healthcare-website-design-examples-synergy.png" alt="healthcare website design examples - synergy private practice" width="720" height="370" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-68820" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/healthcare-website-design-examples-synergy.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/healthcare-website-design-examples-synergy-480x247.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>5. Track your SEO performance</h3>
<p>In addition to reporting on your PPC performance, you should also keep track of your organic/SEO performance. Use Google Tag Manager and GA4 to analyze SEO metrics and customer behavior against your goals, as well as Google Search Console. You can also use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/18/how-to-use-google-data-studio">Google Looker Studio</a> (formerly Google Data Studio) to monitor organic performance.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/google-data-looker-studio-traffic-sources.png" alt="google data/looker studio - traffic source report" width="720" height="173" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-66867" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/google-data-looker-studio-traffic-sources.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/google-data-looker-studio-traffic-sources-480x115.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>6. Reduce your PPC spend with location targeting</h3>
<p>This is a key<a href="https://localiq.com/blog/home-services-marketing-tips/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> home service business marketing tip</a>. One challenge many <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/19/google-ads-for-small-businesses">small businesses face with advertising</a> is a limited budget. One client I worked with had only $10 a day to spend. To overcome this challenge, I used <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/07/google-ads-geotargeting">location targeting</a> to reach a 5km radius around the business‚Äôs location. This approach helped them <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/21/how-to-save-money-google-ads">save their advertising budget</a> while also reaching the right audience.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/save-money-google-ads-location-settings.png" alt="how to save money in google ads - location targeting options" width="720" height="489" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-57568" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/save-money-google-ads-location-settings.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/save-money-google-ads-location-settings-480x326.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>7. Bid on commercial intent keywords</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/21/how-to-run-google-ads">When running Google Ads</a>, you have to tell Google which keyword(s) you‚Äôre bidding on. While there are tons of keywords relevant to your business, the ones to bid on with your PPC campaigns should have high <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/06/30/commercial-intent-keywords">commercial intent</a>.</p>
<p>Do extensive keyword research to identify the keywords that potential customers would be searching for when looking for what you have to offer. Informational intent keywords should be used for SEO. For PPC, use commercial or transactional intent so that your ads won‚Äôt just <em>appear</em> for those searches, but so that they‚Äôll get <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/09/14/improve-google-ads-click-through-rate"><em>clicked on</em></a> by people, and those most likely to convert.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/keyword-intent-four-types.png" alt="the four types of keyword intent" width="720" height="441" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-61610" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/keyword-intent-four-types.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/keyword-intent-four-types-480x294.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>8. Maintain a negative keyword list</h3>
<p>In addition to targeting high commercial intent keywords, be sure to use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/06/06/negative-keyword-guide">negative keywords</a>‚Äîwhich are keywords that you do not want your ad to appear for. This will prevent your ads from showing up for and getting clicked on by people for whom your product or service is not a good fit.</p>
<p>In my view, even with broad match, this is especially important when your daily budget is low.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/google-ads-negative-keywords.png" alt="google ads - add as negative keyword" width="545" height="244" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58391" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/google-ads-negative-keywords.png 545w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/google-ads-negative-keywords-480x215.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 545px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>9. Set up conversion tracking</h3>
<p>Another important aspect of running a Google Ads campaign is measuring your success with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/30/google-ads-conversion-tracking">conversion tracking</a>. With this visibility, you can harness the campaigns, offers, settings, and strategies that are working and eliminate what‚Äôs not and improve your ROAS (Return On Ad Spend).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/conversion-tracking-mistakes-conversion-value.png" alt="google ads conversion tracking - conversion value" width="720" height="204" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-70054" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/conversion-tracking-mistakes-conversion-value.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/conversion-tracking-mistakes-conversion-value-480x136.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Check out our list of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/08/google-ads-conversion-tracking-mistakes">conversion tracking mistakes</a> to make sure you&#8217;re getting the most accurate data possible.</p>
<h2>Improve your local businesses‚Äôs online presence with SEO &amp; PPC</h2>
<p>The best way to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/get-found-online">improve your online presence</a> for your local service-based business is to use SEO and PPC together. Both will help to improve your presence on the SERP for a wide range of keywords, and with the tips I provide, you‚Äôll be able to reach your target audience and build trust and credibility with potential customers.</p>
<p>Here are the tips I mentioned in this post:</p>
<ol>
<li>Pick the right company and domain name</li>
<li>Get your listings in order</li>
<li>Target keywords with blog posts</li>
<li>Put your highest value CTA at the top right of your homepage</li>
<li>Track your SEO performance</li>
<li>Reduce your PPC spend with location targeting</li>
<li>Bid on commercial intent keywords</li>
<li>Maintain a negative keyword list</li>
<li>Set up conversion tracking</li>
</ol>
